<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName LSID="61B84645-EEC9-EF47-C001-B2A6F8ADBEB8" authority="L." authorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Allamanda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allamanda cathartica" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cathartica">Allamanda cathartica L.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="names">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Names.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Myanmar</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">shwe-pan-new</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">shewewa-pan</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">English</emphasis>
: common allamanda, golden trumpet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Origin probably in northern South America, but now widespread in tropical America. Cultivated in Myanmar.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bark</emphasis>
: Hydragogue in ascites. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leaf</emphasis>
: Cathartic (in moderate doses).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
In India the bark is used as a hydragogue for ascites; the leaf as a cathartic (
<bibRefCitation author="Jain, SK" journalOrPublisher="Phytotherapy Research" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" refId="B50" refString="Jain, SK, DeFilipps, RA, 1991. Medicinal Plants of India. 2 Vols. Reference Publications, Inc, Algonac." title="Medicinal Plants of India. 2 Vols. Reference Publications, Inc, Algonac." year="1991">Jain and DeFilipps 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
